      "observation": "step `upgrade_spring_boot_3_3` (jdk=17): BUILD FAILED post-recipe, rc=1\n--- first error cluster ---\n[19:26:52] PROJECT_ROOT=/work/src PHASE=build_post JDK=17\n[ERROR] COMPILATION ERROR : \n[ERROR] /work/src/GapsWeb/src/main/java/com/jasonhhouse/gaps/service/PlexQueryImpl.java:[20,43] package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is not visible\n  (package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is declared in module java.xml, which does not export it)\n[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-compiler-plugin:3.13.0:compile (default-compile) on project GapsWeb: Compilation failure\n[ERROR] /work/src/GapsWeb/src/main/java/com/jasonhhouse/gaps/service/PlexQueryImpl.java:[20,43] package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is not visible\n[ERROR]   (package com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref is declared in module java.xml, which does not export it)\n[ERROR] -> [Help 1]\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] To see the full stack trace of the errors, re-run Maven with the -e switch.\n[ERROR] Re-run Maven using the -X switch to enable full debug logging.\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] For more information about the errors and possible solutions, please read the following articles:\n[ERROR] [Help 1] http://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/MAVEN/MojoFailureException\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] After correcting the problems, you can resume the build with the command\n[ERROR]   mvn <args> -rf :GapsWeb",
      "qwen_observation": "Compilation failed at JDK 17 during Spring Boot 3.3 upgrade because code imports `com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal.dtm.ref`, an internal JDK package encapsulated since Java 9 and not exported in the `java.xml` module.",
      "qwen_rationale": "The `UpgradeSpringBoot_3_3` meta-recipe aggressively updates the parent POM and compiler plugin, triggering stricter module boundary enforcement that blocks access to internal `com.sun.org.apache.xml.internal` packages. Deferring the Spring Boot 3.x migration and first applying `UpgradeBuildToJava17` allows the build to stabilize on Java 17 with the existing parent/compiler configuration. We then re-introduce `UpgradeSpringBoot_3_3` after Java 17 source transforms, giving the compiler a chance to adapt before the full framework migration."
    },
